name: Christmas (CD)
description:
“Christmas” captures both the spirit of Celtic music and the  magical warmth of Christmas.  With soaring, angelic vocals, and lush, warm 
instrumental arrangements, the songs range from the mysterious “Carol of the Bells” to “Jolly Old St. Nicholas” and playful “Little Drummer Girl.”

Track Listing
1. The First Noel
2. Little Drummer Girl 
3. Winds Through the Olive Trees
4. I Saw Three Ships / Marie's Wedding
5. Santa Lucia / Czechoslovakian Carol
6. Carol of the Bells / We Three Kings 
7. Good King Wenceslas 
8. Silver Bells
9. Greensleeves
10. Jolly Old Saint Nicholas
11. Silent Night
12. We Wish You A Merry Christmas

name: Celtic Rainbow (CD)
description:
Celtic Rainbow’s eleven tracks range in style and mood from old Celtic tunes (“Sleepy Maggie, a modernized version of Robert Tannahill’s poem) to pop (in a slightly Celtic-ized version of Miley Cyrus’ “the Climb”) and include strong, flawless instrumentals and soft, sweet vocals.

Track Listing
1. Sleepy Maggie 
2. Taking Flight 
3. The Rocks of Bawn
4. Paddy's Green Shamrock Shores
5. The Climb
6. Orange Blossom Special 
7. Death by Triple Fiddle
8. Both Sides Now
9. Caledonia 
10. Celtic Rainbow 
11. Auld Lang Syne

name: Purple Live Show Poster
description:
Live show pictures and pretty purple design captures the spirit of a live Gothard Sisters show.
Design by Amy Wakefield

name: Green Gothard Sisters Poster
description: A green collector's poster with Greta, Willow and Solana's names and faces on it.

name: Daughters of Erin (CD)
description:
Featuring the Gothard Sisters’ skilled instrumental arrangements, Daughters of Erin covers traditional Irish music, from the beautiful “Hector the Hero” to the  misty “Road to Lisdoonvarna” and features jigs, reels, ballads and waltzes from 
Ireland and the Celtic nations.

Track Listing
1. The Road to Lisdoonvarna
2. Kerry Dance
3. The Minstrel Boy
4. Snow in April
5. Banish Misfortune
6. Cool Silver Boys
7. Si Bheag, Si Mhor
8. Flowers of Edinburgh
9. Hector the Hero 
10. Pachelbel's Frolics
11. Allen the Fisher
12. Celtic Rhythm
13. Auld Lang Syne
14. Smash the Windows
15. The Session
16. Dies Irae
17. Caledonia
18. Star of the County Down
